{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "SHELF/volcano", "tags": "viscousfluids"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Emit Lava"], "extent": [43, 57]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Generates a continuous stream of hot lava from an object."], "extent": [57, 123]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [123, 138], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool will set up a simulation to generate a continuous stream of hot lava from an object. It also applies a lava shader to the result of the simulation. You would typically use this tool to simulate something like a volcanic eruption, or to create a pouring stream of hot lava."], "extent": [138, 423]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [423, 429], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This tool uses a SOP attribute to control the initial temperature of the emitter instead of the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Temperature"]}, " parameter on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/flipobject", "type": "link", "text": ["FLIP Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/flipobject"}, ". "], "extent": [429, 600]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using Emit Lava"], "extent": [600, 622], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "indent": 0, "text": ["Create a geometry object to be converted into lava."], "extent": [622, 678]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "indent": 0, "text": ["Click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/volcano", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHELF/volcano"}, {"type": "ui", "text": ["Emit Lava"]}, " tool on the Viscous Fluids tab. "], "extent": [678, 758]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "indent": 0, "text": ["Select a fluid object to emit lava into, if any, and press ", {"keys": ["Enter"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, "."], "extent": [758, 831], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["For specific parameter information, see the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/flipobject", "type": "link", "text": ["FLIP Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/flipobject"}, " and ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/gastemperatureupdate", "type": "link", "text": ["Gas Temperature Update"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/gastemperatureupdate"}, " help pages."], "extent": [831, 988]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/shelf/emitlava.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [988, 1025]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Tips"], "extent": [1025, 1036], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Turning on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Enable Temperature Diffusion"]}, " checkbox on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/gastemperatureupdate", "type": "link", "text": ["Gas Temperature Update DOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/gastemperatureupdate"}, " will give you parameters that will allow heat form the hot part of the lava to cause cooler parts of the lava to heat up and melt. "], "extent": [1036, 1295], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Radius"]}, " parameter will control how wide the blur radius is for the temperature field."], "extent": [1295, 1397]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Heat/Cold Bias"]}, " will control how much the current temperature is affected by the hotter/cooler temperatures around it."], "extent": [1397, 1529]}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["The ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Solidify Threshold"]}, " parameter on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/gastemperatureupdate", "type": "link", "text": ["Gas Temperature Update DOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/gastemperatureupdate"}, " controls the point at which the lava will solidify. This is meant to simulate how lava will go from a fluid to developing a crust and essentially becoming a rock very quickly.  The higher this value is, the earlier this state change will occur."], "extent": [1529, 1879]}], "container": true}]}], "title": ["Emit Lava"], "summary": ["Generates a continuous stream of hot lava from an object."]}